<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 3:33AM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...LOCALLY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Areas fog have developed across much of the area this morning away
from the coast. The fog could become locally dense at times
through daybreak with visibility dropping to 1/4 mile or less at
times.
The nature of the fog is such that visibilities will vary greatly
over short distances with the risk for locally dense fog being
the greatest near bodies of water and other low-lying areas such
as marshes, swamps and large ditches. Motorists should remain
alert for these conditions this morning.</description>
<instruction>If driving, slow down and leave extra distance ahead of you in
case a sudden stop is needed.</instruction>
